      "iteration": 1,
      "passed": true,
      "critique": "Several significant issues reduce confidence in production readiness: (1) No concurrency protection \u2014 game_manager.py mutates shared dicts/sets (connections, answered_this_round) without asyncio locks, creating race conditions under concurrent WebSocket activity. (2) Disconnect handling is incomplete \u2014 remove_connection() removes the socket but the timer loop still waits for total_players answers (line 267), which can freeze the game if a player disconnects mid-round. Other players are not notified of the disconnect. (3) The integration test for the full 10-question 2-player game (test_complete_game_2_players) uses a fragile message-draining strategy with bare except clauses and hardcoded receive counts that may not match actual broadcast patterns, making tests flaky. (4) The 4-player test only plays one question rather than a full 10-question game. (5) test_final_leaderboard_ranking queries the database directly using asyncio.get_event_loop() which is deprecated and may fail on Python 3.12+. (6) Frontend e2e tests use mocked WebSocket/fetch \u2014 they verify component integration but not true end-to-end behavior against the real backend."
    },
    "symbol": "eval:overall"
  },
